import json import java.io import random from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import StreamCallback from java.lang import System as javasystem
class PyStreamCallback(StreamCallback): def __init__(self): self.id=0 def process(self, inputStream, outputStream): text = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8) jsonObj=json.loads(text) self.id=str(random.choice(range(100000,999999))) jsonObj["id"]=self.id jsonObj["product"]=str(random.choice(["book","toy","lego","blocks"])) jsonObj["price"]=str(random.choice(range(10,99)))+"."+str(random.choice([10,50,89,99])) outputStream.write(bytearray((json.dumps(jsonObj)+"\n").encode('utf-8')))
flowFile = session.get() if (flowFile != None): callback=PyStreamCallback() flowFile = session.write(flowFile,callback) flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile,"orderid",callback.id) session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)

import json import java.io import random from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import StreamCallback from java.lang import System as javasystem
class PyStreamCallback(StreamCallback): def __init__(self): pass def process(self, inputStream, outputStream): text = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8) jsonObj=json.loads(text) newObj={} newObj["id"]=jsonObj[0]["id"] newObj["shipmentid"]=str(random.choice(range(100000,999999))) newObj["shipday"]=str(random.choice(["monday","tuesday","wednesday","thursday","friday"])) outputStream.write(bytearray((json.dumps(newObj)+"\n").encode('utf-8')))
flowFile = session.get() if (flowFile != None): flowFile = session.write(flowFile,PyStreamCallback()) session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
